column1: # NASA Exoplanet Exploration Program Office Internal Database
column9: Hab Zone: both from Kopparapu+2014, adopting either "conservative" or "optimistic" hab zone limits (assume 1 Mearth for calculation)
Planet mass upper limit: "conservative" < 5 Mearth, "optimistic" < 10 Mearth.
Planet radius upper limit: "conservative" < 1.5 Rearth, "optimistic" < 1.8 Rearth
Discovery flag in column 4: K(Kepler mission), K2, RV(radial velocity), T(other transit)
Quantities in italics are calculated in this table from other published parameters
"Conservative temperate terrestrial exoplanet count" = number of likely terrestrial planets (<=1.5 Re, <=5 Me) in conservative habitable zone" ('hall of fame')
"Optimistic temperate terrestrial exoplanet count" = number of likely terrestrial planets (<=1.5 Re, <=5 Me) in optimistic habitable zone" (would include early Venus and early Mars)
"Optimistic temperate small exoplanet count" = number of "small" (<=1.8 Re, <=10 Me) planets in optimistic habitable zone" (likely contains some sub-Neptunes)

column48: Quintana+2014 discovery, updated params from Torres+2015
Astudillo-Defru+2017; revised radius (1.72 Re) from Kane(2018) results in density 8.8 g/cc, hence it is rocky despite large radius
Torres+2015 (also 0.2" bin), no Gaia DR2 plx, Dist from Torres, SpT from Muirhead+2013
Wright+2016 reported, Astuidillo-Defru+2017 confirmed & using their params
Jenkins+2015 reported; Mullally+2018 argues it is unconfirmed. Following NExScI (https://exoplanetarchive.ipac.caltech.edu/docs/kepler452b.html), I've retained the planet for now.
Tuomi+2013 reported; Dias+2016 "current data are not conclusive concerning the existenceƒ"
Torres+2015 (also 0.2" bin), no Gaia DR2 plx, Dist from Torres, SpT from Muirhead+2012
Dittman+2017, large (6.65 Mearth), but retained as M & R consistent with rocky
Muirhead+2012; Two issues: not in DR25 and Torres+2017 lists two close stellar companions (0.164",0.206"), planet may be 2.66 or 2.38 Re if orbiting one of those
Morton+2016,Thompson+2018/DR25; Good agreement among authors T ~ 4000K
Mann+2013 reported; Torres+2017 params; 0.334" binary, 3.14 Rearth if orbiting companion? Not in DR2, Dist from Morton+2016
Vanderberg+2018; single K2 transit; "first temperate planet found in an open cluster". NASA Exoplanet Archive does not list as a planet.
Feroz+2013 and Robertson+2014 could not confirm
Thompson+2018/DR25; Most published Teffs consistent w/4700K, but Muirhead+2012 gets M0V, Teff=3880K (luminosity increases => S increases => too hot for HZ)
Gaidos+2014; no follow-up studies after 2014; NASA Exoplanet Archive does not list as a planet (9/2018)
Feroz+2013 and Robertson+2014 could not confirm
Feng+2017, just a tad outside optimstic HZ

Udry+2007 report; Robertson+2014 & Hatzes+2016 suggest period is artifact of rotation/activity, and Trifonov+2018 couldn't confirm (they agree it is rotation, and retain only b,c,e); signal has been thoroughly refuted, due to stellar activity/rotation. NASA Exoplanet Archive does not list as planet (9/2018)
Gillon+2017 found P=20+15-6, Luger+2017 found P=18.767+0.004-0.003 day.
Gaia DR2 common proper motion pair (WDS J19458+4116) 1.1" away, Hirsch+2017 calls "bound"
Torres+2015 (also 0.2" bin), no Gaia DR2 plx, Dist from Torres, SpT from Muirhead+2011
Gaidos+2014; no follow-up studies after 2014; NASA Exoplanet Archive does not list as a planet (9/2018)
Huber+2014,Mathur+2017 Teff (2703K) was way too cool; Angelo+2017 "exo-Venus"
Barclay+2013 disc., Torres+2017 params (need to update luminosity w/DR2 => further, S higher!). Blend? "super-Venus"

Thompson+2018/DR25; Torres17 lists 1.97+0.19-0.48 Re for c, a=0.2254+0.0092-0.0139, Seff=1.03+0.47-0.61, Teq=286; adopts Teff=4057+251-64K, which seems way too cool. Muirhead+2012 calls it M0V, but T~4550K (~K4.5V)
Borucki+2011; Most indicators consistent with ~K3, but Mather17 & Muirhead12 consistent with early M. I adopt the Morton16 numbers and LAMOSTDR2 SpT
Thomson+2018/DR25; Muirhead+2012 gives M3V Teff=3412K. Frasca+2016 calls K6V (Teff=4971+-241K), Gray+2016 calls it K5IV-V, Johnson+2017 Teff=4804+-65K
Rowe+2014 reported; params from Torres+2017; delta(mag)~8 companion at 3.1" (Torres+2017). "c" = KOI-2650.0.01, not 0.02
